It left a house in ruins and a passer-by who tried to help was injured. The man was found after police were called to reports of an explosion early yesterday.  Lincolnshire Police said the property, in Spalding, suffered "100 per cent damage". It is thought the passer-by suffered burns as he tried to help. Police asked people not to speculate about the cause. A spokesman said: "Officers will remain in the area for the next few days." 